Task: 05
Title: Infrastructure inbound HTTP, DI, and bootstrap
Phase: 1
Route: full
Slice: Passthrough Chat Completion (OpenAI)
Dependencies: 03, 04
Scope: Create the Hono HTTP server and all inbound adapters: server.ts (app factory), OpenAI route (POST /v1/chat/completions with request/response translator for non-streamed JSON), and /v1/models stub route. Wire everything together in the DI container (manual composition root) and bootstrap entry point (main.ts). Create fusion.config.json with a single provider entry for passthrough mode. This task delivers the first runnable end-to-end system: a real OpenAI-compatible client can call the passthrough endpoint.
Acceptance Criteria: AC-2, AC-5 (partial — endpoint working), AC-6 (partial — /v1/models stub)
NFRs: NFR-1, NFR-2
Gate Criteria: Phase 1 Gate 1 (valid ChatCompletion JSON response), Phase 1 Gate 2 (dependency rule verification completed)
Files:
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/server.ts (CREATE) — Hono app factory: creates app, mounts OpenAI routes and /v1/models, exports createServer()
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/openai/route.ts (CREATE) — POST /v1/chat/completions route: parses OpenAI-format body, translates to FusionRequest, calls FusionService.runFusion(), encodes response as JSON
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/openai/translator.ts (CREATE) — Pure functions: openAiRequestToFusion() and fusionStreamToOpenAiResponse() (non-streaming only in Phase 1)
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/models-route.ts (CREATE) — GET /v1/models stub returning a JSON array with at least one model entry from ConfigPort
  - src/infrastructure/di/container.ts (CREATE) — Manual composition root: instantiates config → logger → adapters → use case → routes → server
  - src/main.ts (CREATE) — Bootstrap: imports container, calls createServer(), starts @hono/node-server listener
  - fusion.config.json (CREATE) — Single-provider config (type: "openai", role: "panel") for passthrough mode
